\par \pard\plain \li90\sb80\sl-240 \f6\fs20\lang1033 The main window, initially in the upper left corner of the screen, displays a list of {\ul newsgroups}{\v\uldb newsgroup}
.  Double-clicking on a newsgroup name causes WinVN to display a list of subjects of available {\ul articles}{\v\uldb article} in that newsgroup in a {\uldb group window}{\v group_window}. 
\par Clicking on a newsgroup name "selects" that newsgroup and displays it in reverse video (light on dark).  Selecting a newsgroup is useful only for subscribing to it; see {\uldb Subscribing to Newsgroups}{\v subscribing_to_newsgroups}
.  By default, subscribed groups appear in black; unsubscribed groups appear in blue.  See  
