\par \pard\plain \li90\sb80\sl-240 \f6\fs20\lang1033 When you exit WinVN via the {\uldb main window's}{\v main_window} Network/Exit menu command, you are given the option of saving the configuration options you have set during the session.  (The informati
on is saved to {\uldb WINVN.INI}{\v WINVN.INI}.)  If you haven't changed any configuration options during the session, it doesn't do any harm to save them anyway.  
\par If you change configuration options and want to save them immediately to guard against the computer crashing (yes, this has happened with WinVN!), use the {\uldb Save Configuration}{\v save_configuration} menu command of the main window.
